A bubble of radius $r$ containing a diatomic ideal gas has soap film of thickness $t\ll r$ and is placed in a vacuum. The soap film has surface tension $\sigma$ and density $\rho$. \begin{anum}
        \item Find the molar heat capacity of the gas in the bubble for such a process when the gas is heated so slowly that the bubble remains in a mechanical equilibrium at all times.
        \item Find formula for the frequency $\omega$ of the small radial oscillations of the bubble and evaluate it under the assumption that the heat capacity of the soap film is much greater than the heat capacity of the gas in the bubble. Assume that the thermal equilibrium inside the bubble is reached much faster than the period of oscillations.
    \end{anum}

